note.p:
Pub. L. 114–328, div. A, title VII, § 703(a)(3), Dec. 23, 2016, 130 Stat. 2198, provided that: “In addition to the centers of excellence designated under section 1073d(b)(4) of title 10, United States Code, as added by paragraph (1), the Secretary of Defense may establish satellite centers of excellence to provide specialty care for certain conditions, including with respect to— “(A) post-traumatic stress;
“(B) traumatic brain injury; and
“(C) such other conditions as the Secretary considers appropriate.”
